== Spacecraft ==
The spacecraft uses the [[Space Systems/Loral]] (SSL) [[SSL 1300|1300 bus platform]].<ref name="Oh2017" /> JPL added the [[command and data handling]] and telecom subsystems and all flight software.<ref name="Oh2017" />

=== Propulsion ===
[[File:Hall Thruster for Psyche operating at JPL.jpg|thumb|left|upright=0.8|[[SPT-140]] Hall-effect thrusters undergoing testing at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory.]]

{| class="wikitable floatright"
|-
! SPT-140 !! Parameter/units<ref name='NAS Myers'>{{cite web|url=http://sites.nationalacademies.org/cs/groups/depssite/documents/webpage/deps_085382.pdf|title=Solar Electric Propulsion: Introduction, Applications and Status|publisher=Aerojet Rocketdyne|first=Roger|last=Myers|access-date=January 6, 2018|archive-date=January 7, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180107174824/http://sites.nationalacademies.org/cs/groups/depssite/documents/webpage/deps_085382.pdf|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name='EP conference'>{{cite conference|url=https://iepc2017.org/sites/default/files/speaker-papers/iepc_2017_ssl_electric_propulsion.pdf|title=New Avenues for Research and Development of Electric Propulsion Thrusters at SSL|conference=35th International Electric Propulsion Conference October 8–12, 2017 Atlanta, Georgia|first1=Ian K.|last1=Johnson|first2=Ewan|last2=Kay|first3=Ty|last3=Lee|first4=Ryan|last4=Bae|first5=Negar|last5=Feher|date=2017|id=IEPC-2017-400|access-date=January 6, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180107061615/https://iepc2017.org/sites/default/files/speaker-papers/iepc_2017_ssl_electric_propulsion.pdf|archive-date=January 7, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>
